We chose a very interesting position for discussion.
It is a variant that has recently become a popular gambling variant among russian players
the game we will study was performed by two great players
they are one of the best players in the world
as you know, he got the 2nd place in last WC
the famous position that can also come from d5 opening.
Russian tend to play this opening, even in WC games.
So, we have to be prepared
maybe some of you already know the Russian gambling 6th move?
Indeed, the 6th move they play is g7!
I do not know who actually invented this move,
but now several Russians play it.
What is the idea of this move?
breaking many of possible black lines
why did white play such move?
if back take this point, very powerful?
this move seems like Chines 'bagua', for defending.
In that game, Sushkov played a bit odd 7th move.
The whole pattern looks very wild now.
I suppose, because it was played in year 2000,
Actually, we are not sure this 7th move is good.

Now that you are prepared for this trap,
and there are no big problems,
so we can continue with the game itself
and see what happened between two masters
Klimashin doesnt let the blacks to connect to the 5th move
Black is very patient here, and bearing the white activity
It began to look like white is taking the control
but Sushkov surprised with great 13th move
Now, black has its own VCT threat
What do you think, is black good now?
White will have to sacrifice its last power for defense
seems black can win in the lower side
And now there is nothing left for white
the 20th move is the lowest move that can still defend left side
only if you didnt see that game
can you guess Sushkov's next move?
VCT at low side ans connect to right
vct threat and white has to block inside and black got strong position in lower side
guest625, i dont understand two areas
i meant, this moves connects many areas
i think the upper side is weak
so there is no need to connect there
the move 21 is great by itself
it  makes use of 17-1 to develop right side
Now the strong diagonal attack begins
do not give it to whites
too strong in the right side
say me if you found win
rauni will put on real board
klimashin didnt let sushkov have such beautiful win
its ok, now its yy's turn
so, it is time to make final conclusions of what we learned from this game
first of all, although the 7th move is a big odd,
Sushkov managed to control the game with great 13th and 15th moves
and later on won powerfully thanks to the move 21
it is a very nice example of how a strong world class player can operate in new position
always finding a good way out into a successful position
the idea of 13 15 and 21 is great
